      "Krippendorff's α (ordinal) shows a different pattern: strong for register (α = 0.90) and originality (α = 0.80), moderate for syntactic estrangement (α = 0.75) and imagery (α = 0.64), and poor for coherence (α = 0.17).",
      "The gap between ρ and α reflects systematic calibration bias rather than genuine disagreement. GPT-4o rates higher than Claude on every metric (mean offset 0.67 points), with the largest differences on indeterminacy (1.14) and estrangement (0.94). Krippendorff's α penalizes this constant offset; Spearman's ρ is invariant to it.",
      "Since arguments depend on ordinal patterns (estrangement rising with α, coherence dropping at the phase transition, dual-layer steering accessing a region unavailable to single-layer), rank-order agreement is the more informative measure.",
      "The low coherence α warrants specific comment. GPT-4o assigns 5.0 to nearly all baseline and negative-steering conditions, compressing variance into a narrow band at the scale ceiling. Claude distributes scores more broadly. Despite this difference in dynamic range, both evaluators agree directionally about which conditions produce less coherent output (ρ = 0.68, p < 10⁻²⁸).",
      "Condition-level means confirm that the key trajectories replicate across evaluators. Both models show estrangement increasing monotonically with α, coherence dropping sharply between α = 6.0 and α = 7.5, and dual-layer compositions achieving higher estrangement than single-layer steering at comparable coherence."
